Download -> Create a Folder -> cd <folder-name> -> $ git init

GIT LIFE CYCLE WORKS AT THE BACKENDS:
WORKING DIR -> CHANGES DONE -> ADD/REMOVE <-> STAGING AREA -> COMMIT CHANGES -> LOCAL REPOSITORY -> REMOTE REPOSITORY

LAB-1
HOW WE CAN CREATE THE BRANCHES ?
$ git branch							# list all the branches
$ git checkout <branch-name>			# switch to an existing branch 
$ git checkout -b <branch-name>		# automatically create a new branch and switched
$ ls -l 
$ git add .
$ git commit -m “added all source like master”	# 
$ git push origin <branch-name>		# push the changes to new branch

COMPARE AND PULL REQUESTS:
We want to merge the latest changes to any branch
DevOps -> New pull req -> Valid comments -> Create pull requests -> A POP would be appear to ur Git Admin
Team Lead -> Merge pull requests -> Confirm merge 

GitHub Desktop Tool:
Install and play

DELETE THE BRANCH FROM LOCAL:
$ git branch							# List the existing branch
$ git branch -d <branch-name>			# delete the existing branch
$ git branch -D <branch-name>			# delete the existing branch
$ git branch							# cross verify

DELETE THE BRANCH FROM REMOTE:
$ git branch 
$ git push origin - -delete <branch-name>		# VVImp

SUDDENLY NEED TO SWITCH TO DIFFERENT BRANCH:
$ git branch										# DevOps branch
$ vi <test-file>
$ git status
$ git add .
$ git commit -m “added some changes in <branch>”
Later
$ git push origin DevOps

GIT FETCH COMMAND:
$ git branch
$ git checkout master
$ git pull origin DevOps						# Already up to date.
Later
$ git pull origin DevOps						# List the latest changes
OR
$ git fetch 
$ git pull 
$ git push 					# no need to pass like $ git push origin master

